1. *Silazi* s vrha planine i obrati pažnju na kamenjar ispod sebe. (Descend from the top of the mountain and pay attention to the rocky terrain below you.)
2. On *silazi* niz stepenice i nestaje iz vidokruga. (He goes down the stairs and disappears from sight.)
3. Moramo da *silazimo* niz ovaj strmi put oprezno. (We need to descend this steep path carefully.)
4. Kada *silazimo* nizbrdo, obično brže vozimo. (When we go downhill, we usually drive faster.)
5. Koliko *silazi* naša cena, toliko raste potražnja za proizvodom. (The lower our price goes, the higher the demand for the product.)
6. *Silazimo* na zemlju, pripremi se za sletanje. (We are descending to the ground, prepare for landing.)
7. Sunce *silazi* na zapadu, a izlazi na istoku. (The sun sets in the west and rises in the east.)
8. Ova nova informacija *silazi* u korist našeg tima. (This new information works in favor of our team.)

Note: In Serbian, "silazi" is the third person singular form of the verb "sići" which means "to descend" or "to go down". It can also be used in different tenses and forms such as "silaziti" (imperfect), "silazio" (past tense), "silaziće" (future tense), etc.